Will go to jail if buffalo race ban isn't lifted: K'taka MLA.
As the clamour for ban on jallikattu to be lifted increases, Karnataka too has joined the protest bandwagon demanding ban on kambala be revoked.Supporters of kambala which is a traditional sport played by people from coastal Karnataka have said that they are ready to go to jail to lift the ban on kambala.Many of the animal rights groups have compared kambala to jallikattu and that led to the Supreme Court banning both the bull-taming sports earlier.Also Read: After jallikattu, Mangaluru braces to protest against ban on buffalo racing event Kambala